Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The Japanese encephalitis transmission season in Taiwan is well underway with a total of 9 cases so far this season. More cases can be expected. The mosquito species, _Culex tritaeniorhynchus_, and other related _Culex_ species are efficient vectors of JEV and breed in wet areas such as rice paddies. These _Culex_ mosquitoes are abundant enough there to accomplish transmission of the virus from birds and swine to people. Vector control is difficult. JE is a vaccine-preventable disease. It is not stated whether the affected individual above had been vaccinated. The only measures to prevent infection are vaccination and avoidance of mosquito bites. - Mod.TY

Maps of Taiwan: http://www.mapsofworld.com/taiwan/taiwan-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7551332,193]
